A Concise History of Indian Art
Praeger Publishers | 1976 | ISBN: 0275856208 | English | 264 pages | PDF | 67.6 MB

Much of what is known of the history of Indian art is of comparatively recent scholarship, and even more work awaits future studies. The work which defined the field was Ananda K. Coomaraswamy's History of Indian and Indonesian Art, published in 1927. Though the book is now somewhat outdated, anyone involved with the art of India owes a fundamental debt to Coomaraswamy and must ultimately come to regard him as their scholarly patriarch
